      "narr_en": "In 970, the Fatimids founded al-Azhar Mosque and its attached madrasas in Cairo. Originally established to spread Ismaili Shia doctrine, al-Azhar evolved into the most prestigious educational institution of Sunni Islam. Considered one of the world's oldest universities with over a millennium of uninterrupted teaching tradition, al-Azhar remains today among the foremost religious-academic authoriti",
