      "narr_en": "From 1065 onward, Great Seljuk vizier Nizam al-Mulk founded the Nizamiyyah Madrasas in Baghdad and many other cities. These madrasas marked the beginning of systematic curriculum, regular scholarships, and state-sponsored education in Islamic educational history. Great scholars like Imam al-Ghazali taught at the Nizamiyyah. The madrasa system was an institutional educational revolution thought to ",
