      "narr_en": "In 1099, the First Crusade captured Jerusalem. The European knights massacred the Muslim and Jewish population upon entering the city. The loss of Jerusalem, under Islamic rule for approximately 450 years, sent shockwaves through the Muslim world. Fatimid weakness and political fragmentation in the Islamic world were the fundamental reasons for Crusader success. This event prepared the ground for ",
