      "narr_en": "In 1187, Saladin retook Jerusalem after 88 years, following his victory at Hattin. Unlike the massacre during the First Crusade, Saladin accepted the city peacefully and allowed Christian inhabitants to leave upon payment of ransom. This conduct is cited in both Islamic and Western historiography as an example of chivalry. The reconquest of Jerusalem generated great jubilation in the Muslim world ",
