      "narr_en": "In 1259, the great scholar Nasir al-Din al-Tusi, vizier to the Mongol Ilkhanid ruler Hulagu, established the most advanced observatory in the Islamic world at Maragha. Astronomers from different religions (Muslim, Christian, Buddhist) worked together here. The Maragha Observatory produced new astronomical theories that corrected Ptolemy's planetary model; the 'Tusi couple' mechanism developed by a",
