      "narr_en": "Around 1420, Timurid prince Ulugh Beg established the last great observatory of the Islamic world in Samarkand. The star catalog produced here recorded positions of over 1,000 stars with the most accurate astronomical observations of the era. Ulugh Beg's trigonometric tables were used as references for centuries. Symbolizing Central Asia's intellectual revival after the Mongol destruction, the obs",
