      "narr_en": "In 785, Umayyad emir Abd al-Rahman I began construction of the Great Mosque of Cordoba on the site of an old Visigothic church. Expanded over the following two centuries, the mosque, with its forest of double-tiered horseshoe arches, became one of Islamic architecture's most original structures. The Cordoba Mosque was the symbol of Islamic Spain and a unique synthesis of Islamic and Roman-Visigoth",
