      "narr_en": "In 936, Andalusian Umayyad caliph Abd al-Rahman III began constructing the palace city of Madinat al-Zahra near Cordoba. Designed as a display of power against the Abbasids and Fatimids after his declaration of the caliphate, this massive project was completed over ten years with thousands of workers and artisans. Adorned with marble, ivory, gold and precious stones, the palace was one of the most",
