      "narr_en": "From the 12th century onward, Toledo became a major center where Arabic scientific works were translated into Latin. In this city, captured by Christian Castile in 1085, Arab, Jewish and Christian scholars worked together translating the works of Aristotle, Avicenna, al-Khwarizmi, Averroes and others into Latin. This translation movement carried the Islamic world's interpretations of ancient knowl",
