      "narr_en": "Molla Khusraw was one of the most important authors of Ottoman Hanafi jurisprudence. His Durar al-Hukkam served as a foundational textbook in Ottoman madrasa education for centuries. He rose to the position of Shaykh al-Islam during the reign of Mehmed the Conqueror. His Mirat al-Usul in legal theory was also an indispensable text in the madrasa curriculum. He is considered one of the figures who laid the foundations of the Ottoman legal system.",
