      "narr_en": "Mohammed Arkoun was a French-Algerian Islamic thinker known for his critical and historical readings of Islamic thought. He developed the concept of 'Applied Islamology' to reread Islamic intellectual history through modern humanities methodology. He taught Islamic intellectual history at the Sorbonne for many years. Through concepts of the 'unthought' and 'unthinkable,' he questioned the boundaries of Islamic thought.",
