      "narr_en": "Haji Bayram Veli was one of the most influential sheikhs of Anatolian Sufism and the founder of the Bayramiyya order. Born in Ankara, he conducted his spiritual guidance there. The large number of his disciples attracted Ottoman attention, and he met Sultan Murad II, earning his trust. Akshamsaddin was his most famous student. His tomb and mosque in Ankara remain among the city's most important spiritual sites.",
