      "narr_en": "Al-Jahiz was one of the greatest authors of Arabic prose literature, known for al-Bayan wa al-Tabyin and Kitab al-Hayawan. Affiliated with the Mutazili theological tradition, he treated topics of rhetoric, zoology, sociology, and psychology in a literary style. His Kitab al-Bukhala is a masterpiece of satirical literature on miserliness. He was one of the most brilliant intellectuals of Abbasid Baghdad.",
