      "narr_en": "Ibn Faris was one of the most original lexicographers of Arabic linguistics, known for his Mujam Maqayis al-Lugha. This dictionary is a unique work analyzing the etymological roots of Arabic words. By identifying the core semantic nucleus of each word, he systematically revealed the internal structure of the language. His al-Sahibi fi Fiqh al-Lugha is also an early example of philosophy of language. He lived in Hamadan and Ray.",
